               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>This manuscript contains the beginning of the <title xml:lang="sa">Rājamartaṇḍa</title>, a text on <term xml:lang="sa">Ayurveda</term> attributed to the 11<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>-century king <persName xml:lang="sa">Bhoja</persName>. The copy is unfinished, breaking off in the middle of the fifth chapter.</p>
<p>Unusually, the folios are made from thin sheets of birch bark, cut into pothi format. This manuscript seems to have been made by <persName>Palmyr Cordier</persName>; the modern <term xml:lang="sa">Devanāgarī</term> script is in his hand, which can also be found on the many title cards he made for other manuscripts.</p></summary>
                  
